","dimension":17,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.036538,0.065656,0.080083,0.092945,0.095751,0.098949,0.10192,0.10114,0.097726,0.089191,0.077372,0.062721],"unified_progress":[0.035579,0.06544,0.083917,0.094456,0.10031,0.10525,0.10395,0.10078,0.094702,0.089032,0.073364,0.053233]},{"section":10,"text":"CD5 is usually associated with T-cells, but in some B-cell malignancies, like chronic lymphocytic leukemia (CLL), a subset of B-cells can express CD5.","dimension":15,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.029021,0.052683,0.069205,0.082277,0.096139,0.1029,0.11008,0.11077,0.10578,0.095333,0.080884,0.064926],"unified_progress":[0.0337,0.063427,0.083423,0.094124,0.1015,0.10721,0.1059,0.10196,0.095812,0.089026,0.072134,0.051777]},{"section":11,"text":"The high percentage of these cells in the blood\u201480%\u2014is significant.","dimension":1,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.030455,0.060054,0.080601,0.092447,0.099673,0.10146,0.10096,0.098453,0.09471,0.088827,0.080396,0.071958],"unified_progress":[0.039189,0.071961,0.087677,0.096252,0.1018,0.10027,0.10179,0.094425,0.09001,0.083016,0.073537,0.060075]},{"section":12,"text":"CLL often presents with lymphocytosis, and the cells have a characteristic appearance on flow cytometry.","dimension":1,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.038756,0.06191,0.074289,0.084618,0.094521,0.09863,0.10117,0.10017,0.096624,0.088666,0.0837,0.076945],"unified_progress":[0.046756,0.076342,0.087138,0.092778,0.098193,0.099573,0.10152,0.093876,0.088954,0.082563,0.073348,0.058954]},{"section":13,"text":"The bright kappa light chain suggests that these B-cells are expressing kappa, which is typical for CLL.","dimension":1,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.029097,0.057075,0.075426,0.090655,0.10055,0.10473,0.10527,0.10269,0.098359,0.0886,0.078879,0.068661],"unified_progress":[0.037982,0.07272,0.09046,0.098629,0.10491,0.1028,0.10681,0.093963,0.088617,0.080344,0.069454,0.053313